      looking from time to time at that apprehensive lady, doating on her
      terrors. And Mr. George seconded her by his clouded face, for he was
      ashamed not to show that he did not know Louisa Harrington in the Countess
      de Saldar, and had not the courage to declare that he did. The Countess
